						<div class="postbody">...and testing again City Trouble with this knowledge, I note that I can crash it on startup via reset. Even though it is consistently safe at power on for me, reset is not. (I was not testing reset before.)<br /><br />So I think on some systems, the power on state will give a ~100% chance of failure of the test, and on other systems (like mine) it's ~100% chance of success.<br /><br />Reset, on the other hand seems to have like a ~10% chance of failure, now that I'm looking at it! (This probability is likely consistent across a lot of systems.)<br /><br />I think this is actually a sufficient explanation for the problem!</div>

